==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*juz'', representing Indo-European ''*yūs''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[ji|jī]], Old Saxon [[gi]] (Dutch [[gij]]), Old High German [[ir]] (German [[ihr]]), Old Norse [[ér]] (Swedish [[i]]), Gothic [[𐌾𐌿𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Albanian [[ju]], Baltic ''*ju-'' (Lithuanian [[jus|jũs]]), Tocharian A ''yas'', B ''yes''.

